<p id="d1e6640">We discuss the optimal control problem 
 <xref rid="fd14" ref-type="disp-formula">(14)</xref> in a more general context. We use the notation 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e6647" display="inline" altimg="si161.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-italic">x</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">=</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">S</mi>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">E</mi>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <msub>
      <mrow>
       <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">I</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">P</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <msub>
      <mrow>
       <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">I</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">A</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <msub>
      <mrow>
       <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">I</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">S</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">R</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. We look at the optimal control problem 
 <disp-formula id="fd15">
  <label>(15)</label>
  <math id="d1e6704" display="block" altimg="si162.svg">
   <mfenced open="{">
